WEBVTT

00:00.962 --> 00:03.626
All right, I need a little help this morning if you're willing to enable.

00:04.307 --> 00:08.254
In just a second, I'm going to put a few lyrics from a song on the screen.

00:08.875 --> 00:14.043
And I'd like for you, if you can, help me fill in the last line or the next lyric that's coming.

00:14.063 --> 00:14.504
Here we go.

00:16.647 --> 00:17.869
Romeo saved me.

00:17.909 --> 00:20.433
They're trying to tell me how to feel.

00:21.715 --> 00:24.800
This love is difficult, but it's real.

00:25.942 --> 00:26.903
Don't be afraid.

00:26.963 --> 00:28.626
We'll make it out of this mess.

00:30.498 --> 00:33.762
It's a love story, baby just say yes.

00:36.546 --> 00:38.529
Now for some of you, you might be wondering what is that?

00:38.970 --> 00:43.175
Those are the lyrics, some of the lyrics from Taylor Swift's love story.

00:44.057 --> 00:47.822
A song from 2008, it's actually a really, it's a pretty creative song.

00:48.643 --> 00:54.190
What she's done is taken the story of Romeo and Juliet and she's trying to give it a happy ending.

00:55.092 --> 00:59.698
So instead of death, she has Romeo get down on his knee and propose

01:00.130 --> 01:03.636
And the idea is that they sort of live happily ever after.

01:04.818 --> 01:20.483
But the interesting thing about even teenage Taylor Swift's idea of love is that although she's tried to give it a happy ending, even in the song you heard it in the lyric, this love is difficult, but it's real.

01:21.365 --> 01:27.154
The idea is you can't take all of the cost out of love, or it's not love anymore.

01:28.130 --> 01:34.220
You can't take the suffering out, you can't take the difficulty out, or it's no longer love.

01:34.881 --> 01:54.834
And even if you want to give a happy ending, in the song it's still clear that Juliet's dad doesn't want Romeo around, that Juliet feels alone and difficulty in this whole thing, and that no matter what, as happy as it might be, for love to be something,

01:55.298 --> 02:00.664
It has to actually mean something, and for it to mean something, it has to cost something.

02:02.146 --> 02:04.729
All love involves sacrifice.

02:06.951 --> 02:09.094
You see, this is the Sunday before Christmas.

02:10.616 --> 02:16.943
And at Christmas, we think about hope, peace, joy.

02:18.905 --> 02:23.090
But sometimes at Christmas, we forget that it's ultimately about love.

02:24.194 --> 02:26.056
The Christmas is a love story.

02:26.957 --> 02:30.280
It's a love story between God and us.

02:32.883 --> 02:38.209
And that sometimes you can actually have hope without it costing you anything.

02:41.032 --> 02:44.775
You can feel at peace without it costing anything.

02:46.077 --> 02:51.122
You could just wake up in the morning and be filled with joy for no reason and it doesn't cost you anything.

02:53.346 --> 03:02.177
But it's impossible to be loved and to love without it costing something.

03:04.079 --> 03:08.665
Last week we explored the most momentous truth in all the universe.

03:10.647 --> 03:14.132
God is love.

03:15.914 --> 03:19.218
But we didn't define what is love.

03:21.826 --> 03:30.194
Well, this morning we get to come to understand that what makes love love is that there is a cost involved.

03:31.555 --> 03:44.588
There is a sacrifice required, that if we take away all the difficulty, if we take away all the negativity, if we take away all of the hard endings, we're not left with love at all anymore.

03:46.470 --> 03:50.834
And so this morning, this Christmas, we want to be reminded that ultimately Christmas

03:51.010 --> 03:55.940
is a love story of how God loves us.

03:57.142 --> 03:59.427
And we want to come to understand that better.

03:59.467 --> 04:05.519
So let me invite you, if you're willing, to take a Bible and turn to the book of 1 John chapter 4.

04:06.020 --> 04:09.006
If you don't have a Bible with you, there's one in the rack in front of you.

04:10.469 --> 04:13.234
In those Bibles, it's page 988.

04:17.634 --> 04:22.800
In the same way, we might put Taylor Swift's lyrics on the screen so that we can see them and read them together.

04:23.220 --> 04:27.685
We're opening up our Bibles because it's worth reading what God has written to us.

04:28.426 --> 04:34.653
In many ways, these are lyrics to a beautiful, perfect love song from God to us.

04:34.713 --> 04:38.117
And so invite you, if you've never even opened a Bible, just take one.

04:38.137 --> 04:40.900
It just looks like this from in front of the rack in front of you.

04:41.621 --> 04:46.066
Turn to page 988, which is a letter from Apostle John.

04:47.042 --> 04:55.694
We're in chapter four in the church Bibles, that's on the left hand column of page 988, and we're gonna read verses seven to 10.

04:56.695 --> 04:59.059
So last week we looked at this whole passage.

04:59.579 --> 05:03.024
This week we're just going to focus on verses seven through 10.

05:04.086 --> 05:05.948
First John chapter four, page 988.

05:06.229 --> 05:10.855
This is what God says to us through the Apostle John.

05:10.915 --> 05:15.762
Dear friends, let us love one another for love comes from God.

05:17.186 --> 05:20.591
Everyone who loves has been born of God and knows God.

05:21.593 --> 05:29.224
Whoever does not love does not know God because God is love.

05:31.087 --> 05:33.610
This is how God showed his love among us.

05:34.432 --> 05:38.357
He sent his one and only son into the world that we might live through him.

05:39.519 --> 05:40.420
This is love.

05:41.202 --> 05:44.146
Not that we loved God, but that he loved us.

05:44.738 --> 05:49.302
and sent His Son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.

05:50.584 --> 05:53.907
We said last week that all love comes from God.

05:54.888 --> 05:59.452
That any love that exists in the world has ultimately God as its source.

06:00.753 --> 06:06.138
That even human love can give us some vision of what God's love is like for us.

06:06.679 --> 06:14.226
So Taylor Swift is as good a guide as any in the non-Christian world of seeing things that we can learn about love.

06:14.818 --> 06:23.167
And even a teenage Taylor Swift comes to recognize there is no such thing as love without a cost.

06:23.187 --> 06:32.297
Now as we think about this, in Taylor Swift's song, Love Story, she tells the story from Juliet's point of view.

06:33.759 --> 06:40.967
There's a little bit of Romeo at the end, but it's essentially her story, and so she's telling it from Juliet's point of view.

06:41.948 --> 06:43.570
God has written this passage,

06:44.194 --> 06:49.059
And he's effectively telling us his love for us from his point of view.

06:49.719 --> 06:55.725
So while this morning we could talk about Jesus' love for us because he absolutely does love us.

06:56.266 --> 07:00.070
And he did all that was asked of him because he loves us.

07:00.950 --> 07:05.595
But this passage is written to tell us how God the Father loves us.

07:06.856 --> 07:10.360
And he shows us this love in two ways.

07:11.501 --> 07:12.882
First, verse nine,

07:13.954 --> 07:16.417
what we traditionally think of as Christmas.

07:17.358 --> 07:20.242
He shows us his love in Jesus becoming human.

07:21.383 --> 07:24.647
And then in verse 10, what we traditionally think of as Easter.

07:26.189 --> 07:33.838
God the Father shows us his love in the death of Jesus Christ, his son on a cross.

07:33.878 --> 07:43.890
And so this morning, as we are reminded that it cost God something to love us, we want to think about God's love for us

07:44.514 --> 07:51.321
in terms of what God has done for us at Christmas and what God has done for us at Easter.

07:52.583 --> 07:54.785
So we begin in verse nine with Christmas.

07:56.847 --> 08:00.051
This is how God showed his love among us.

08:01.492 --> 08:09.120
He sent his one and only son into the world that we might live through him.

08:10.202 --> 08:14.386
Now one of the great things about studying or reading an entire book of the Bible

08:14.626 --> 08:25.724
It's like listening to a song and listening to all the lyrics and not just a few, is that when you get the context of everything that's being written, you have a better understanding of what the individual parts mean.

08:26.685 --> 08:34.057
Well, we have a better understanding when it says that God loved us by sending his son into this world.

08:34.618 --> 08:39.506
We have a better understanding because we've been looking at the book of 1 John for most of the year.

08:40.258 --> 08:59.417
And what we've come to understand is as God says that when He sent His Son into this world, He's not just talking about the created world, this beautiful world that we live in, a world of trees, of stars in the sky, of moonlight and serene lakes and beautiful hills.

09:01.319 --> 09:08.626
He also sent His Son into a world that's full of cultures and societies and technologies and governments.

09:09.442 --> 09:15.189
that are under, according to 1 John, the control of the evil one.

09:15.209 --> 09:16.871
The whole world is under control.

09:17.191 --> 09:23.579
This is the world that God the Father is choosing to send His Son into.

09:23.619 --> 09:31.749
Into a world that is antagonistic to God and will be antagonistic toward His Son.

09:32.690 --> 09:39.378
That God is making the choice to send Jesus into this world.

09:40.674 --> 09:44.279
that's under the control of his enemy, Satan.

09:45.982 --> 09:57.699
And so in verse nine, we want to understand that from God, the father's point of view, there was a great cost involved in choosing to send his son.

09:58.961 --> 10:10.418
In fact, this morning, I'd like to share with you seven things that cost God something in the choices he made of sending his son

10:10.850 --> 10:13.013
to become human, to live among us.

10:14.917 --> 10:31.383
The first is that God the Father chose to place Jesus into this world in circumstances that appeared to be incredibly shameful from a sin point of view, meaning this.

10:33.546 --> 10:38.354
Even an angel had to come and tell Joseph that Mary hadn't been unfaithful.

10:39.202 --> 10:40.905
because everybody thought she had.

10:42.026 --> 10:46.313
I mean, after all, here's a woman who's not married, who's pregnant.

10:47.435 --> 10:53.805
And her betrothed is like, well, there's only one explanation for that because I didn't sleep with her.

10:55.087 --> 10:59.935
An angel has to come and say, no, Joseph, what is in her is a baby, which is from God.

10:59.975 --> 11:03.981
Now, it's hard enough today to believe that Jesus was born of a virgin.

11:05.364 --> 11:06.866
Imagine 2,000 years ago.

11:08.194 --> 11:10.898
before anybody knew who Jesus was going to be.

11:14.042 --> 11:23.435
You see, the evidence for the shameful nature of this is that we often say at Christmas time that He was born in a stable because no room for Him at the inn.

11:24.937 --> 11:29.423
But then you go back and you realize, 2,000 years ago there were not a lot of holiday inns.

11:31.706 --> 11:37.874
It wasn't like Joseph forgot to book something, knowing it was census, and then gets on Airbnb and realizes everything is gone.

11:38.274 --> 11:39.535
And he's just going to kind of show up.

11:39.555 --> 11:41.257
This is not how the world worked back then.

11:43.420 --> 11:45.042
Joseph is from Bethlehem.

11:46.143 --> 11:47.725
That's where his relatives live.

11:50.408 --> 11:56.435
When it says there's no room for him at the end, the NIV has shifted the translation to say there was no guest room available for him.

11:58.377 --> 12:00.319
None of his relatives want them to stay with him.

12:03.943 --> 12:06.226
I mean, beyond that.

12:07.618 --> 12:12.603
Hospitality is an important thing in Middle Eastern culture, especially 2,000 years ago.

12:13.785 --> 12:19.511
Can you imagine anybody seeing a pregnant woman about to give birth and being like, uh, you should stay in the manger?

12:21.854 --> 12:30.683
The only reason anybody would do this is if they think the mom and the kid are cursed because of sin.

12:32.305 --> 12:36.690
These are the circumstances that God, the father, places his son into.

12:37.218 --> 12:44.710
Joseph knows and Mary knows, but everybody else thinks that this is a shameful birth.

12:47.054 --> 12:54.285
Second, God chooses to place his son into a poor family.

12:55.026 --> 12:56.789
Jesus grows up in poverty.

12:58.071 --> 13:04.882
We know this because, again, in the Old Testament, when you were given a baby, you said thank you to God by giving and offering.

13:05.762 --> 13:14.693
And there were two choices, either the upper class and middle class offering, which was the lamb, or there was the poor class offering.

13:15.975 --> 13:22.263
And that was you gave a pigeon, because anybody could go out, catch a pigeon, and sacrifice it.

13:24.586 --> 13:29.472
The birth of Jesus Mary gives a pigeon, because her and Joseph are poor.

13:31.075 --> 13:33.778
Jesus grows up in poverty.

13:35.234 --> 13:47.610
Third, God the Father chooses to place Jesus in a situation where at His birth, He's an enemy of the state.

13:49.172 --> 13:51.495
Even before He's born, Herod wants to kill Him.

13:52.897 --> 13:59.986
Herod is so desperate to kill Him that He searches everywhere for Jesus and when He can't find Him, even before Jesus is even potty drained.

14:01.410 --> 14:08.060
Herod orders all the babies in the general area who are too and under killed in his attempt to get to Jesus.

14:10.304 --> 14:29.554
Four, because they are enemies of the state, early on Mary, Joseph, and baby Jesus have to travel to Egypt to get away from Herod in the Middle East, which makes Jesus a refugee.

14:30.850 --> 14:32.192
seeking political asylum.

14:33.294 --> 14:36.680
He grows up in a culture that is foreign to him and to his parents.

14:37.421 --> 14:47.759
And some of you may remember you where we did a series on race and ethnicity about a year and a half ago, we talked about the fact that Egyptians at that time discriminated against Hebrews.

14:49.181 --> 14:51.385
They discriminated against Jews, they didn't like them.

14:54.751 --> 14:56.594
And Jesus is first years of his life.

14:58.338 --> 15:04.145
are lived in a culture that is antagonistic towards him, discriminates against him.

15:04.165 --> 15:10.151
Where there is no family, no friends, no one to help them.

15:10.171 --> 15:22.666
Fifth, God places his son, Jesus, into a family where it appears that the adoptive father, Joseph, dies relatively early on.

15:24.187 --> 15:26.610
Which means that Jesus is raised by a single mom.

15:27.874 --> 15:33.100
with all of the challenges and difficulties in which that results in being that situation.

15:33.921 --> 15:37.525
Jesus grows up fatherless in that situation.

15:38.105 --> 15:43.932
Number six, God also places Jesus into a family in which his siblings are antagonistic towards him.

15:45.153 --> 15:47.015
Jesus has half brothers and sisters.

15:47.456 --> 15:51.761
They're half brothers because Jesus' father is God and his mother is Mary.

15:53.363 --> 15:56.466
His siblings have Mary as a mother and Joseph as a father.

15:57.538 --> 16:06.592
But those siblings, the Bible tells us, were antagonistic towards Jesus, mocking him, insulting him, trying to work against him, obeying his father.

16:08.575 --> 16:14.403
And then seven, Jesus is placed into a situation where he is misunderstood by everyone.

16:15.445 --> 16:17.668
We have one story from when Jesus is 12 years old.

16:18.289 --> 16:21.554
His parents don't seem to understand what he's up to and what he's supposed to be doing.

16:22.175 --> 16:24.459
When he grows up, his disciples don't understand him.

16:24.859 --> 16:26.802
The religious leaders don't understand him.

16:27.330 --> 16:29.393
The people of the culture don't understand him.

16:29.413 --> 16:31.156
His own family doesn't understand him.

16:31.196 --> 16:33.920
He is misunderstood by everyone.

16:35.563 --> 16:44.857
Now again, we can talk about these as the sufferings and the love of Jesus for us that he was willing to do this.

16:44.877 --> 16:55.954
But if you've ever loved somebody, you understand something of the suffering that God the Father went through because he chose

16:56.130 --> 17:00.377
to place Jesus in these difficult situations.

17:01.959 --> 17:10.092
You see, sometimes we think that Jesus lived a wonderful life and just kind of had a really bad last week.

17:10.112 --> 17:12.696
Like he just got to show up as God in the flesh.

17:12.736 --> 17:13.838
He did a bunch of miracles.

17:13.878 --> 17:15.140
He walks around on water.

17:15.160 --> 17:16.021
He's like, hey, look at this.

17:16.121 --> 17:17.584
And hey, look, I'll make a bunch of food.

17:17.844 --> 17:19.006
And I'm gonna heal a bunch of people.

17:19.286 --> 17:20.769
And yeah, life is fantastic.

17:20.789 --> 17:24.274
And then, oh, last week, terrible week, but okay, got through that.

17:26.082 --> 17:34.213
No, the truth of the matter is Isaiah says that Jesus lived a difficult life from the day he was born until the day he would die.

17:34.553 --> 17:34.994
He died.

17:35.534 --> 17:40.881
He was a man of sorrows, well familiar with suffering.

17:40.902 --> 17:43.805
It wasn't like the last week showed up and he was like, what is this?

17:45.528 --> 17:50.835
Now it was just the culmination of an entire life that was incredibly difficult to live.

17:52.937 --> 17:53.458
And again,

17:54.466 --> 17:58.290
Jesus loves us by being willing to do this.

17:58.310 --> 18:09.321
But if you've ever loved somebody, you're far more willing to take the bad stuff on yourself than to ask somebody else that you love to go through those things.

18:11.603 --> 18:22.674
God, the Father was willing to do this and ask Jesus to do these things, to go through a difficult life because He loves you.

18:24.226 --> 18:24.807
And he loves me.

18:27.449 --> 18:29.391
That's verse nine, verse 10.

18:29.411 --> 18:31.033
That's Christmas, verse 10 Easter.

18:31.734 --> 18:41.043
This is love, not that we loved God, but that he loved us and sent his son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.

18:42.665 --> 18:51.954
We say it's not just that Jesus had a really hard week, he had a hard life, but he also had a really, really hard week at the end of his life.

18:52.578 --> 18:56.102
a ridiculously hard week.

18:56.122 --> 19:08.095
Three things to say about the suffering that God the Father went through in Jesus' last week.

19:08.115 --> 19:16.103
Number one, He sent His Son as an atoning sacrifice for our sins.

19:18.706 --> 19:22.450
I can only imagine the grief and the pain

19:24.418 --> 19:33.246
from God the Father as he's watching Jesus pray in the Garden of Gethsemane.

19:33.266 --> 19:53.586
If there was ever a prayer that God was desperate to answer, if there was ever a prayer he so badly wanted to do, it was the prayer of his perfect, beautiful, amazing son who had done everything that the Father had asked him to do.

19:54.210 --> 20:00.079
that in the Garden of Gethsemane, Jesus with tears in his eyes is begging his Father.

20:00.440 --> 20:02.683
Please don't make me go through this.

20:03.845 --> 20:13.480
Please, if there's any other way, he is distraught, crying out to God to the point of death.

20:14.521 --> 20:17.806
Please, Father.

20:17.826 --> 20:20.210
And I have to imagine of all the prayers ever prayed.

20:22.113 --> 20:22.834
That's the one.

20:23.714 --> 20:25.577
God the Father most wanted to answer.

20:30.463 --> 20:31.024
But He didn't.

20:33.728 --> 20:34.048
Why?

20:37.133 --> 20:37.994
Because He loves you.

20:39.576 --> 20:40.197
And He loves me.

20:43.341 --> 20:47.307
And so the hardest know that He'd ever had to give.

20:48.929 --> 20:49.350
He gave.

20:51.072 --> 20:52.594
So that you and I could have life.

20:57.186 --> 21:05.457
Second, he sent his son as an atoning sacrifice.

21:05.477 --> 21:15.491
Another passage says, God the Father made Jesus who knew no sin to be sin for us.

21:17.333 --> 21:20.818
And I have to imagine what did it cost God the Father?

21:22.402 --> 21:27.007
to let Jesus become the thing that he hates.

21:28.929 --> 21:30.190
God hates sin.

21:31.572 --> 21:32.793
He hates injustice.

21:33.874 --> 21:34.815
He hates bitterness.

21:34.875 --> 21:35.756
He hates anger.

21:35.796 --> 21:36.998
He hates selfishness.

21:37.558 --> 21:48.170
Jesus never did any of those things, but at his death, God placed on Jesus our selfishness, our bitterness, our anger.

21:48.530 --> 21:52.274
And Jesus became the very thing that God hates.

21:55.874 --> 22:08.411
And as terrible as the physical suffering was, the far greater suffering is at the moment that Jesus needs him the most.

22:11.255 --> 22:25.554
The moment when his precious one and only son is all alone and cries out, Father, why have you forsaken

22:27.970 --> 22:42.285
At that moment, God the Father has to turn his back because Jesus has become, at God's choosing, the very thing that God cannot stand.

22:44.988 --> 22:45.948
He did that for us.

22:48.471 --> 22:55.218
So hard as this to understand that even today, some people want to accuse God the Father of cosmic child abuse.

22:56.514 --> 22:58.356
How could anybody do this?

23:02.061 --> 23:03.604
There's no logical explanation.

23:03.644 --> 23:06.567
There's no rational explanation.

23:06.588 --> 23:12.936
The only possible explanation is because he loves you and he loves me.

23:14.879 --> 23:16.761
And there simply wasn't another way.

23:17.863 --> 23:21.608
This is what it cost for us to have life.

23:25.533 --> 23:26.354
And then finally,

23:27.074 --> 23:30.237
He sent his son as an atoning sacrifice.

23:32.499 --> 23:35.522
In Christianity, we use the word sacrifice so much we forget what it means.

23:37.224 --> 23:40.387
A sacrifice is a sacrifice.

23:41.108 --> 23:42.549
It costs something.

23:44.431 --> 23:47.874
It costs the one who is giving the sacrifice.

23:47.894 --> 23:50.317
God the Father is giving Jesus.

23:50.837 --> 23:53.060
Jesus is his sacrifice.

23:53.100 --> 23:55.602
He is sacrificing something.

23:55.938 --> 23:59.262
for Jesus to come, for Jesus to die.

24:01.024 --> 24:06.390
Some of us think, oh, well, Jesus kind of became human for 30, 35, 40 years.

24:06.911 --> 24:07.972
Okay, that's a tough stretch.

24:08.012 --> 24:08.713
I'll grant you that.

24:09.614 --> 24:12.197
But in eternity, while the 40 years, that's not so bad.

24:15.661 --> 24:23.730
But the reality as verse nine says, he sent his one and only son into the world that we might live through him.

24:25.762 --> 24:34.394
Because our life is tied to Him being human, Jesus did not become human for 30 or 40 years.

24:37.719 --> 24:41.504
He became human forever and ever.

24:43.487 --> 24:46.171
There's no undoing this.

24:46.191 --> 24:47.192
There's no going back.

24:49.576 --> 24:54.002
We continue to live because He's human.

24:56.354 --> 25:05.906
And we will never fully understand the sacrifice that God the Father made in asking Jesus to become human for eternity.

25:09.470 --> 25:11.953
But He did it for us.

25:16.098 --> 25:22.546
As much as we might wish that there was love without sacrifice, there is no such thing.

25:26.818 --> 25:40.897
So if you hear nothing else this Christmas season, if nothing else goes well, if everything about this season is horrendous, worse than you could have possibly imagined.

25:40.917 --> 25:41.898
I want you to know this.

25:45.063 --> 25:45.664
You are loved.

25:47.446 --> 25:49.429
You are totally and completely loved.

25:52.473 --> 25:53.394
At every point,

25:54.402 --> 25:58.927
God the Father chose brutally difficult, hard things.

26:00.389 --> 26:03.392
He sent Jesus to become human.

26:03.412 --> 26:13.483
He asked His precious Son to go through the worst life imaginable and die the most horrific death that anyone has ever died.

26:16.727 --> 26:19.670
Because He loves you and He loves me.

26:20.851 --> 26:23.474
God has shown His love

26:24.738 --> 26:25.439
in doing this.

26:28.204 --> 26:28.965
Not Christmastime.

26:30.307 --> 26:31.589
We often think of giving presence.

26:33.012 --> 26:38.080
That comes from the fact that God is love and God demonstrates His love by giving Jesus.

26:40.604 --> 26:41.906
But I want you to think for a moment.

26:44.418 --> 27:03.997
that if you've drawn the name of somebody, or there's somebody that you love that you're gonna buy a present for, and you have spent all year thinking about this present, and you've put a bunch of money into it, and you put a bunch of time into it, and a bunch of effort into it, and you've wrapped it all up, and you've placed it beneath the tree, and you can't wait for Christmas morning, because you know, this present is fantastic.

27:04.677 --> 27:06.119
It's gonna change their life.

27:08.841 --> 27:13.746
How would you feel if someone says, no, I'm not open to that present?

27:16.226 --> 27:18.609
How would you feel if they said, yeah, no, thank you.

27:18.649 --> 27:19.350
I'm not interested.

27:21.573 --> 27:27.020
Even if it had really nice terms, like, I'm not worthy of that, or I don't deserve a present.

27:27.040 --> 27:28.362
I haven't been good enough this year.

27:28.402 --> 27:29.344
How would you feel?

27:30.325 --> 27:31.607
The present's already bought.

27:32.388 --> 27:33.289
It's under the tree.

27:34.110 --> 27:35.732
The cost has already been paid.

27:36.773 --> 27:38.616
You didn't do it because they deserved it.

27:38.636 --> 27:40.058
You did it because you loved them.

27:41.099 --> 27:46.226
How would you feel if at that moment, when you hand them the present, they say, no, thank you.

27:50.626 --> 27:55.411
What God is saying is, I've already bought the present.

27:56.392 --> 27:59.276
Jesus has already become human for eternity.

28:00.177 --> 28:01.838
Jesus has already gone through these things.

28:01.878 --> 28:03.360
He's already died on a cross.

28:03.700 --> 28:09.867
Long before you and I were born, God prepared this present, wrapped it up and has placed it under the tree.

28:09.947 --> 28:15.954
And this Christmas, He is saying to you, this is my present to you because I love you.

28:20.706 --> 28:23.229
and as noble as the response may be, but I'm not worthy.

28:24.151 --> 28:25.192
I've messed up too much.

28:28.016 --> 28:30.579
The truth of the matter is the present's been purchased.

28:36.127 --> 28:50.706
And all you gotta do, the right answer is the same answer you want if you've bought somebody a present that costs you a ton, that can't be returned, that was done out of love for you.

28:51.458 --> 28:55.603
The right response is, thank you.

28:58.666 --> 28:59.647
That's all God's looking for.

29:01.730 --> 29:05.674
He just wants you to accept the present.

29:05.694 --> 29:07.837
And you do that by you just say, thank you in your heart.

29:10.200 --> 29:13.603
Because some people are like, well, I'll take the present because I feel so because I'll just never use it.

29:14.104 --> 29:15.826
It's already been purchased.

29:20.002 --> 29:22.685
God did it because there wasn't any other way for us to have life.

29:24.146 --> 29:26.709
There wasn't any other way for us to be with Him.

29:28.571 --> 29:31.413
And so He asked His Son to do these things for our sake.

29:35.397 --> 29:40.042
Now for some of us here this morning who are already Christians, we've accepted the present and we're grateful.

29:40.062 --> 29:40.803
We got the present.

29:40.843 --> 29:41.643
We opened the present.

29:41.664 --> 29:43.145
We're like, this is amazing.

29:43.245 --> 29:43.746
Thank you.

29:46.288 --> 29:48.210
But there's a danger with Christmas presents.

29:50.210 --> 29:57.702
And that is if you open the present and you maybe you've had it for a little while, sometimes you start to wish it was a different present.

30:00.567 --> 30:03.091
Now I don't think any of us here want somebody other than Jesus.

30:04.994 --> 30:06.176
But here's what I mean by that.

30:08.861 --> 30:11.004
Sometimes you wish the president didn't cost so much.

30:13.688 --> 30:17.074
Sometimes you wish the president didn't involve so much struggle and suffering.

30:19.010 --> 30:29.364
Because by accepting the present, you're also thinking to yourself, well, now I'm going to have to give something back.

30:32.468 --> 30:34.111
I'm going to have to give something that costs me.

30:37.695 --> 30:42.282
What we wish, especially at Christmas, is that there's no cost.

30:43.243 --> 30:43.964
It's just all easy.

30:43.984 --> 30:44.505
It's all free.

30:47.569 --> 30:48.370
But that's not love.

30:50.658 --> 30:54.843
And some of us look at God and wish that the present He got us didn't have so much suffering.

30:54.883 --> 30:57.345
So the presence we give Him don't have to have that much suffering.

31:01.130 --> 31:04.153
We want God to just make all the mental health issues that we have go away.

31:05.434 --> 31:07.377
We want God to just heal us of all of our sickness.

31:07.397 --> 31:12.242
We want God to provide all full employment whenever we want to work with plenty of good salary.

31:12.442 --> 31:13.864
We want God to provide the relationship.

31:13.884 --> 31:15.465
We don't want to struggle with loneliness.

31:15.506 --> 31:16.527
We don't want to be single.

31:16.787 --> 31:19.570
We don't want the gift to cost this much.

31:23.970 --> 31:30.921
And so one of the dangers for people who have already accepted the gift is that we forget how much the gift costs.

31:33.885 --> 31:35.628
And the truth of the matter is this Christmas.

31:38.512 --> 31:43.400
If we're going to love God in return, it's going to cost us something.

31:45.784 --> 31:49.970
If we're going to love others, it's going to cost us something.

31:52.738 --> 32:00.091
Even Taylor Swift figured out, if you take all the costs out of love, it's not love anymore.

32:02.836 --> 32:18.002
And for some of us this Christmas season, we just need to be reminded that God has loved us enough to ask us to pay something to love others and to love Him in return.

32:22.498 --> 32:23.099
God is love.

32:24.801 --> 32:26.122
What does it mean to love?

32:26.162 --> 32:28.364
Love costs.

32:29.866 --> 32:36.173
There's always sacrifice associated with love at Christmas and at Easter.

32:37.494 --> 32:40.578
God has shown how much he loves us.

32:42.680 --> 32:45.403
He gave his son so that we might have life.

32:47.245 --> 32:51.730
He asked his son to die so that we might have life forever.

32:52.994 --> 32:57.882
This is love, not that we loved God, but that He loved us.

32:59.244 --> 33:10.322
If you take nothing else away this Christmas season, even if you don't open the present, please know that you are love.

